@startuml adr-supabase-native-rev2
title Supabase-native (Rev 2): Identity -> Perm Context -> RLS, and Slice-1 Constraint Emission

' ===========================================================================
' PART A: identity flow (resolves C1, C2, C3, C4)
' ===========================================================================

package "Sign-in & Identity (GoTrue)" {
  class GoogleSignIn {
    + id_token (engine) / access_token (web CRM)
  }
  class GoTrue {
    + issues session JWT
    + runs custom_access_token_hook on every mint
  }
  class CustomAccessTokenHook {
    + match lower(email) -> public.users / tabUser
    + inject claims: app_user_id, branch, role
  }
  class tabUser {
    + name : text (= email, canonical)
    + email : text
    + branch : text
    + enabled : boolean
    --
    + auth_user_id : uuid  <<NEW, FK auth.users(id)>>
  }
}

GoogleSignIn --> GoTrue : verify (server-mediated:\ncreateUser + generateLink/verifyOtp)
GoTrue --> CustomAccessTokenHook : on token mint
CustomAccessTokenHook --> tabUser : lower(email) lookup
tabUser ..> "auth.users" : auth_user_id (back-filled,\nnullable, additive)

' ---- engine server path (service-role, RLS bypassed) ----
package "Engine server path (trusted, service_role)" {
  class ctxFromRequest {
    + verify bearer
    + iss==Supabase -> Supabase JWKS (NEW)
    + else -> Google JWKS (transition)
  }
  class identity_resolveUserToCtx {
    + store.get tabUser + tabHasRole
    + build Ctx{user, roles, scopes.branch, unrestricted}
  }
  class queryConditions {
    + branch scope + owner filter
    + unrestricted(admin) -> no filter
    + PRIMARY enforcer (engine callers)
  }
  class SupabaseStore_PgStore {
    + SERVICE_ROLE / direct-PG
    + RLS BYPASSED here
  }
}

GoTrue --> ctxFromRequest : session JWT (bearer)
ctxFromRequest --> identity_resolveUserToCtx
identity_resolveUserToCtx --> queryConditions
queryConditions --> SupabaseStore_PgStore : scoped reads

' ---- non-engine path (anon/auth key, RLS enforced) ----
package "Non-engine path (browser / installer / portal)" {
  class AnonAuthClient {
    + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY + GoTrue JWT
    + auth.uid()/auth.jwt() POPULATED
  }
  class RLS_Policy_tabCustomer {
    + service_role: using(true)
    + authenticated:\n  branch = jwt.branch\n  OR owner = jwt.app_user_id\n  OR jwt.role = admin
    + REPRODUCES queryConditions
    + RLS = ONLY enforcer here
  }
  class tabDocType {
    + ... existing meta cols ...
    --
    + rls_policy_name : text  <<NEW, C4>>
    + permission_intent : text  <<NEW, C4>>
  }
}

GoTrue --> AnonAuthClient : session JWT
AnonAuthClient --> RLS_Policy_tabCustomer : carries jwt claims
RLS_Policy_tabCustomer ..> tabDocType : named by rls_policy_name
RLS_Policy_tabCustomer ..> CustomAccessTokenHook : reads jwt.branch / jwt.app_user_id

note as DisjointNote
  C3 - DISJOINT guard sets (not a cross-check):
  * Engine callers run queryConditions, bypass RLS
    -> a queryConditions bug has NO DB net.
  * Non-engine callers never run queryConditions
    -> RLS is their ONLY protection.
end note
queryConditions .. DisjointNote
RLS_Policy_tabCustomer .. DisjointNote

' ---- test client (C2): sole RLS coverage, OUTSIDE the Store hierarchy ----
class "scripts/rls-probe.mjs" as RlsProbe {
  + raw supabase-js, ANON key
  + signs in test user via GoTrue (real claims)
  + SOLE RLS coverage; not in Store hierarchy
  + positive (own branch sees rows) + negative
}
RlsProbe --> RLS_Policy_tabCustomer : tests positive + negative

' ===========================================================================
' PART B: slice-1 constraint emission (resolves C6, C7) - emitted from ONE meta
' ===========================================================================

package "Meta = single source of truth (adr-meta-as-data)" {
  class tabDocField {
    + fieldname, fieldtype
    + reqd : boolean
    + unique : boolean
    + options : text (Link/Table target)
    + fetch_from : text
  }
}

package "Two outputs from the SAME meta (DRY: emitted, not re-authored)" {
  class "JS validators (friendly message)" as JsValidators {
    + validateAgainstMeta: reqd/Select/numeric/Check/unique
    + validateLinks: Link existence
    + field-level error at engine boundary
  }
  class "ddl.js emitter (fail-fast DB net)" as DdlEmitter {
    + UNIQUE index   <- field.unique        (C6)
    + FK             <- Link.options target  (C6, closes TOCTOU)
    + create trigger <- set_doc_stamps()     (C7)
    + NOT NULL / CHECK : DEFERRED (B.4, with reasons)
  }
  class set_doc_stamps {
    + BEFORE INSERT/UPDATE
    + modified = now() (AUTHORITATIVE)
    + creation = coalesce(creation, now())
  }
}

tabDocField --> JsValidators : read by
tabDocField --> DdlEmitter : read by (SAME rows)
DdlEmitter --> set_doc_stamps : create trigger per table
DdlEmitter ..> tabUser : (Link FK skipped for stub/unregistered targets)

note as DryNote
  DRY stance: one rule lives in the META rows.
  JS gives the friendly field-level message;
  the DB constraint is the fail-fast / least-privilege net.
  The constraint is EMITTED from meta, never authored twice.
end note
JsValidators .. DryNote
DdlEmitter .. DryNote

' ===========================================================================
' O1 / Contract note
' ===========================================================================
note as O1Note
  O1 verdict: Zod is used for DEF structure (def-schema.js)
  and REQUEST envelopes (request-schemas.js) ONLY.
  Entity data is validated by hand-rolled meta-driven JS
  (validateAgainstMeta / validateLinks) - NOT Zod.
  => Contract section 4.1 "Zod is the only validation" must be amended.
end note
JsValidators .. O1Note

@enduml
